thnography, history, folklore, literature, and botany to provide a panoramic account of the multifaceted influence of Afro-Atlantic cultures in Cuba. Cabrera details the natural and spiritual landscape of the Cuban monte (forest, wilderness) and discusses hundreds of herbs and the constellations of deities, sacred rites, and knowledge that envelop them. The result is a complex spiritual and medicinal architecture of Afro-Cuban cultures. This new edition of what is often referred to as “the Santería bible” includes a new foreword, introduction, and translator notes. As a seminal work in the study of the African diaspora that has profoundly impacted numerous fields, Cabrera’s magnum opus is essential for scholars, activists, and religious devotees of Afro-Cuban traditions alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican diaspora. 0aBlack peoplezCubavFolklore. 0aBlack peoplezCubaxReligion. 0aFolklorezCuba. 0aMagiczCuba. 0aSanteriazCuba. 0aTraditional medicinezCuba. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aCastellanos, Isabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFont-Navarrete, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzwed, John F, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008